I was afraid this meat loaf might be dry from the reviews I did the following: equal parts of veal, pork and beef,stale italian bread crumbs made from day old bread (not quite 2/3 cup) and before baking I shook Worshire Sauce all over meat loaf. It was great! I'd make it again

Rating: 3
I agree with some of the other reviewers that this meatloaf was a little dry. I did not follow the recipe exactly which may have been the cause. I used whole wheat bread and added caraway seeds to make the breadcrumbs like rye. I also had more ground beef than pork. In any event, we loved it and would definitely make it again.

Rating: 2
I agree with some other reviewers: I like my meatloaf moist and juicy. This recipe, although unique in ingredients, creates a very dry meatloaf. I think the sauce would be better with lamb or a falafel.

